      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical R2022R1 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented V&V test suite. FDA in-house Python pre/post-processing scripts are under version control (Git) with peer review. DePuy Synthes simulation team operates under ISO 9001-certified QMS. Software qualification records available. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS and Ansys verification manual were executed for beam bending, contact mechanics, and large-deformation plasticity. All benchmark results within 1% of analytical solutions. Code verification documented in simulation plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change < 2% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on pedicle screw shank and rod junction. Stiffness QoI changed 3.1% (coarse to medium) and 0.9% (medium to fine). Fine mesh selected; discretization error estimated at < 1% via Richardson extrapolation. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms and energy balance checked; iterative convergence criteria documented.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson solver with force residual tolerance 1e-4 and displacement residual tolerance 1e-4. Energy balance error < 0.1% across all load steps. Automatic time-stepping with bisection on non-convergence. Solver error assessed as negligible relative to other uncertainty sources."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup by a second analyst not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "Model setup (geometry, boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions) independently reviewed by a second FDA engineer. Discrepancies in screw-rod interface contact formulation identified and corrected prior to final runs. Review checklist archived in simulation record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented and justified relative to physics of ASTM F1717 compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "Implicit quasi-static analysis with large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON) adopted. Screw-rod interface modelled as frictional contact (mu=0.2, augmented Lagrange). Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V represented by bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.14 GPa) consistent with ASTM F136 material data. UHMWPE block modelled as linear elastic (E=0.94 GPa) — validated assumption for sub-yield block deformation regime. Model form consistent with prior FDA FEA guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs traceable to measured or published material and geometric data; input uncertainty characterised.",
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs derived from manufacturer CAD files (DePuy Synthes) verified against CMM measurements on three production screws (max deviation 0.04 mm). Material properties sourced from MMPDS-12 and supplier certificates. A screening sensitivity exercise ranked screw shank diameter, rod diameter, and friction coefficient as the top three influential inputs; their uncertainties were propagated via ±2-sigma bounds in supplementary runs, confirming QoI sensitivity within the accepted tolerance. Input uncertainty documented in simulation plan appendix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N >= 10 specimens from production lots; geometric measurements confirm conformance to nominal dimensions.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production hardware. Specimens sourced from two independent production lots (lot A: n=6, lot B: n=5). CMM measurements of screw outer diameter and rod diameter confirmed all within ±0.05 mm of nominal. UHMWPE blocks cut from single billet to minimise inter-specimen material variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios or at least two independent test conditions are evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition (5° offset, 10 mm offset block). Dynamic fatigue and alternative offset conditions not included in this validation study. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged as a residual limitation of the current validation scope and is documented for regulatory transparency. The submission proceeds under the accepted-with-notation pathway."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters demonstrably equivalent to test specimen parameters within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FEA model geometry updated to per-specimen CMM measurements for each of the 11 specimens. Material properties held at nominal MMPDS values; inter-lot material variation assessed as < 2% on yield strength. Boundary condition equivalency confirmed by comparison of measured machine compliance against model boundary stiffness. Input equivalency documented specimen-by-specimen in simulation record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (percent difference and normalised error E/uval) computed for each QoI; all metrics within pre-defined acceptance bounds.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement. Percent differences: 4.2%, 6.8%, 5.1% — all < 10% bound. Normalised errors E/uval: 0.87, 1.41, 1.02 — all < 1.96 bound. Statistical equivalence confirmed. Output comparison factor achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory decision metrics.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to clinical load-sharing between implant and bone graft. Yield force is the primary regulatory metric for pedicle screw mechanical performance per FDA guidance. Force at 40 mm displacement characterises post-yield energy absorption relevant to revision surgery risk. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the intended COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and boundary conditions match or bound the COU scenario.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the exact device geometry, material, and test standard (ASTM F1717) specified in the COU. Two independent laboratories provide cross-laboratory reproducibility evidence. The validation scenario is directly representative of the COU; no extrapolation required. Relevance factor achieved level 3."
    }
  ],
