    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for model risk level 3. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and documented; the single static ASTM F1717 condition is judged sufficient for the current regulatory decision given corroborating experimental evidence across two laboratories and the Medium model influence and decision consequence ratings. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance bounds (< 10% difference, E/uval < 1.96). The FEA modeling framework is accepted for the stated COU.",
